// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p05/pass.test — P5 helper return types per
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` §3 lines 282–288 + research §5 numeric
// model + the contract topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: `#define X _int(_pow(2.0, 8.0))` → `256`.
//
// P5 chain exercised:
//   1. `_pow(2.0, 8.0)`  — both args real; returns real (256.0).
//   2. `_int(256.0)`     — coerces real to integer via truncate-
//                          toward-zero; returns 256.
//   3. `%X%` at use site — splices the integer literal `256`.
//
// Per FR-019 + P7, the intermediate float MUST NOT cross the seam;
// the `_int(...)` wrapper reduces it before substitution. Per P5,
// the resulting token at the seam is a `tk_decimal_lit` with
// spelling `256` — NOT `256.0`, NOT a `tk_*_lit` with a Z/X/U flag.
//
// This is also FR-017's "single source-of-truth" check for the
// helper closed set: `_int` and `_pow` are both in
// `include/nsl/Basic/HelperSet.def` (T005). Removing either entry
// would fail to recognize the helper at preprocess time.
//
// Tasks.md T041 + spec.md US2 acceptance #3.
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer sees
// `_int(_pow(2.0,8.0))` literally and tokenizes `_int` as
// `tk_system_function` (per N11 `_`-prefix dispatch), the parens as
// punctuation, etc. The float `2.0` lexes as `tk_decimal_lit 2` +
// `tk_dot` + `tk_decimal_lit 0` — there's no float lexer at M1
// (correctly: floats are preprocess-only per P7). Phase-4's helper
// evaluator turns it green.

// RUN: echo '#define X _int(_pow(2.0, 8.0))' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg buf = %%X%%;'               >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// At the use site `%X%` splices the integer literal 256.
// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}buf
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_assign{{[ \t]+}}=
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}256
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_eof

// Floats and helper calls MUST NOT cross the seam (P7 + P12):
// CHECK-NOT: tk_dot
// CHECK-NOT: tk_system_function{{[ \t]+}}_int
// CHECK-NOT: tk_system_function{{[ \t]+}}_pow
